[{"id":"VR871922","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following cross sectional views best represents the charge distributions on the two spheres when they are near each other?</p>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\">\n\t<colgroup>\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:35\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:70\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:70\" />\n\t</colgroup>\n\t<thead class=\"thead\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row rowsep:1\">\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col1\">&nbsp;</th>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span></th>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi> </math></span></span></th>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</thead>\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly around its inner surface.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g05.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly around its inner surface.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g07.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly through its volume.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g21.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly around its inner surface.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g11.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly through its volume.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g23.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly around the right half of its inner surface.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g15.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly around the left half of its inner surface.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g17.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere with negative charges distributed evenly around the right half of its inner surface.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871922.g19.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR871922_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Small solid Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> is made of an insulating materi